and, in particular, it is /not/ true that

|> Math
    \sqrt{x^{2}} \rt{0.1} = \rt{0.1} x

for every real number `x`{math}. Instead we have

|> Math
    \sqrt{x^{2}} \rt{0.1} = \rt{0.1} |\rt{0.08}x\rt{0.08}|
